data.description: Lovely 4 sided brick home features a covered front porch, oversized 2 car garage and large lot near downtown Lawrenceville. New roof Sept. 2020, exterior painted in 2020, interior painted in July of this year, new water heater this year. Very spacious family room with wainscoting, brick fireplace and bay window.  Large kitchen features tile flooring and stainless appliances with a bayed breakfast room and French door leading to the private back yard. Separate dining room and a 1/2 bath with tile floors complete the 1st floor.  Owner's suite and 2 additional bedrooms are upstairs. The owner's suite features 2 large walk-in closets, en-suite bath and extra room that can be used as an office.  Owner's bath has a separate garden tub and shower, tile flooring and double vanity.  The 2 secondary bedrooms are a nice size, and one features a walk-in closet.  The 2nd floor also features another full bath with tile floor.  Spacious back yard has a shed for storage, and the large patio is great for entertaining.  The 2 car garage is oversized with extra storage and the driveway allows for plenty of parking.  Very close to downtown Lawrenceville with restaurants, shopping, festivals and entertainment for everyone.
